HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 257
By Powers
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Farmers Helping
Farmers initiative and its leader, Dan Pearman,
for their remarkable efforts in assisting fellow
farmers in East Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens and initiatives that have contributed significantly to the
betterment of their communities; and
WHEREAS, one such initiative is the Farmers Helping Farmers relief effort, which began
with a heartfelt post from Dan Pearman, who wanted farmers in Cocke and Greene counties to
know they were not alone in the aftermath of the terrible devastation brought by Hurricane
Helene in September 2024; and
WHEREAS, Dan Pearman, along with farmers in Claiborne County, organized efforts to
gather hay and supplies for farmers in Greene and Cocke counties, lining up approximately 500
rolls of hay and a significant amount of feed and other essentials; and
WHEREAS, some fifteen trucks loaded with supplies soon pulled out from Mays'
Loadout Barn on Highway 63 bound for Cocke County, with the commitment that this would not
be the last convoy, and that future efforts would focus on Greene County as well; and
WHEREAS, Dan Pearman's leadership and the spirit of "farmers helping farmers" have
inspired countless individuals to come together, providing hope and support to those affected by
adverse conditions; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Pearman was recently recognized at the Tennessee Cattlemen's
Association convention in Murfreesboro, receiving the John Bartee Distinguished Service Award
for his leadership in organizing multiple hay convoys to Cocke, Greene, and Unicoi counties to
assist livestock producers with feeding their animals in the aftermath of Hurricane Helene; and
