WHEREAS, in total, over 130 loads of donated hay, feed, and other supplies were
provided to the affected farmers, demonstrating the power of community and collective effort;
and
WHEREAS, having recently experienced a couple of life-threatening medical conditions,
Dan Pearman felt a divine calling to help, and his efforts, along with the generous contributions
of many others, resulted in substantial relief for those in need; and
WHEREAS, the Farmers Helping Farmers initiative to assist recovery efforts in East
Tennessee after Hurricane Helene involved some 125 people in Cocke County, 190 people in
Greene County, and 140 people in Unicoi County, who collectively donated hay, time, and other
resources; and
WHEREAS, the actions of Dan Pearman and the Farmers Helping Farmers initiative
stand as a testament to the power of dedication, compassion, and leadership, and they are
wholly deserving of the respect and admiration of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the Farmers Helping Farmers initiative and Dan
Pearman for their outstanding efforts in assisting fellow farmers in East Tennessee and extend
to them our best wishes for continued success in all their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
